I don't seem to be able to get the "Create issue on atom/atom" button to work on Windows 7 x64 (atom 0.161.0),  I can generate an exception in atom by opening a text file in another application that has locked it (Hex Editor) then asking atom to save the file.  When the exception box appears i click on the create issue button but nothing happens. Looking at process explorer i don't see any new processes appear when i click the button.  Also, nothing seems to be output in the developer tab either, so it is more like it isn't doing anything.  

@benogle as requested on issue #4499 I have tried both with IE and chrome open in the background already running and nothing appears.

